item.title: About
item.description: About Me I am a 4th year PhD student in the Computer Science Department at CMU, where I am advised by Weina Wang. Broadly-speaking, I’m interested in queueing theory and stochastic analysis. Right now, I’m a visiting student at the Simons Institute. Research Interest queueing theory, stochastic systems, approximation algorithms, reinforcement learning, applied probability Publications Weina Wang, Anupam Gupta, Jalani K. Williams (random author order) ITCS, 2022.: Probing to minimize
